½ΌRarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2026-03-06-twin0341.mdΌ@36ac4c33d4849d33a7068d2aa4c89d3df77482ba6033a0790f2c1bef1eb10853Ό"title: 'This week in Nushell #341'ëßNushellΎϋ@fdncred:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17728] added testbin "bins" to nushell help (#17728)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17727] fixed duplicate custom commands from showing up (#17727)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17718] fixed the off-by-1 jump scrolling in 
``explore``
 when searching (#17718)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17699] reverted 17606 to make plugin handling more robust on startup (#17699)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17692] removed bad 
``which``
 test and created a better one (#17692)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17691] fixed one-off up/down arrow wrapping bug (#17691)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17680] updated the sqlite history timestamp and duration with nushell values (#17680)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17678] pinned trash to 5.2.4 to avoid needing --locked for macOS builds (#17678)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17677] fixed pipefail issues with complete and let (#17677)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17675] fixed interpolation without closing paren (#17675)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17668] expanded custom value handling to more commands (#17668)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17663] allowed 
``clip copy``
 to copy tables without ansi escapes (#17663)
@ayax79:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17723] implemented selector commands for numeric types in Polars (#17723)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17722] added 
``polars selector ends-with``
 (#17722)
@ChrisDenton:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17721] fixed tests ending cwd with a / (#17721)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17720] preferred PWD over current_dir if they're the same directory (#17720)
@cptpiepmatz:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17716] bumped kitest & removed 
``RefUnwindSafe``
 from experimental option markers (#17716)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17702] updated winresource versions (#17702)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17682] bumped patch after release (#17682)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17681] updated readline version, bumped minor version, fixed some feature conflicts (#17681)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17664] moved native 
``clip``
 commands behind an experimental option (#17664)
@Tyarel8:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17707] added ctrl+p/n for navigation in 
``input list``
 (#17707)
@Juhan280:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17706] added 
``metadata_ref``
 and 
``metadata_mut``
 methods to 
``PipelineData``
 (#17706)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17703] added 
``str escape-regex``
 (#17703)
@blindFS:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17696] fixed respect for 
``reorder-cell-paths``
 option in assignments (#17696)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17684] fixed parser handling of record keys parsed as strings (#17684)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17673] added type inference for cell paths (#17673)
@NotTheDr01ds:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17672] reworked another deprecated 
``metadata set``
 example (#17672)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17667] updated 
``metadata-set``
 example to use 
``--path-columns``
 syntax (#17667)
@app/dependabot:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17710] bumped actions/upload-artifact from 6 to 7 (#17710)
